# FORJD Cursor Rules

## Core Philosophy
- Prioritize stability, security, and lightness.
- Use latest stable versions with security focus.
- Keep everything lightweight, auditable, and production-ready.
- Minimal dependencies. Clear structure. Fast iteration.

## Project Naming
- Backend: forjd-backend / backend
- Frontend: forjd-frontend / frontend
- Overall platform: FORJD
- Keep naming technical and precise.

## Python / Backend Rules
- Python 3.12+
- Use uv for dependency management.
- Core stack: FastAPI + Prefect 3 + Pathway + Dragonfly (redis) + Postgres.
- Async-first, strong typing, Pydantic v2.
- Folder structure: app/core, app/api/v1, app/pipelines, app/models, app/services.

## Angular / Frontend Rules
- Use latest stable Angular (v18+).
- Standalone components + Signals by default.
- Build our own UI library from scratch (forjd-ui).
- No heavy external component libraries (avoid Angular Material for core primitives).
- Focus on:
  - Clean, dense, operational UI (inspired by Cloudscape + previous Viking-UI).
  - Accessibility (WCAG AA) from day one.
  - Consistent theming (SCSS variables, design tokens).
  - Reusable primitives: buttons, cards, tables, forms, workflow canvas, live metrics.
- Folder structure: `libs/forjd-ui/` for the library, then consume in `frontend`.
- Use Angular's library generation (`ng generate library`).
- Prioritize performance, tree-shakability, and customizability.
- Keep it lightweight — only add complexity when clearly needed.

## General UI Philosophy
- Precision over flashy design.
- Operational density (metrics, status, projections).
- Dark-first theme with high contrast.

## Docker Rules
- Multi-stage builds mandatory.
- Prefer distroless or slim base images for final stage.
- Non-root user (USER 1001).
- Minimal final image size.
- Use specific stable tags.

## Workflow & Streaming
- Prefect 3 for configurable, versioned workflows.
- Pathway for high-performance real-time streaming.
- Clear separation: FastAPI for API, Prefect for orchestration, Pathway for stream processing.

## Security & Stability
- Strict input validation on backend.
- CORS, rate limiting, secret management.
- Structured logging.
- Health checks and readiness probes.
- Update dependencies regularly but cautiously (`uv lock --upgrade`).

## Updating Strategy
- One major component at a time.
- Always test after updates.
- Prefer stable channels.

## LOG.md Purpose & Format
- LOG.md is a detailed development journal for future writing (book, articles, etc.).
- When making changes, append a short but informative entry.
- Format:
  - `- YYYY-MM-DD: Brief description of what was done and why (1-2 sentences max)`
- Be specific enough to remember the journey (commands, decisions, challenges).
- Example: `- 2026-07-14: Initialized backend with uv + FastAPI + Prefect + Pathway. Chose Prefect for better Pythonic workflow config over Airflow.`

Follow these rules by default unless explicitly overridden.